                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> it solves at least one important problem (file conflicts).", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": " Could you\n> please list all problems with it so that I can ask Matthias how we can\n> make it usable for both python-central and python-support?\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Of course, its not possible to list all problems without actually\ntrying to implement it.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " At first sight, my main issues with it are:\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "      * XB-Python-Version: current is broken; moving it in a file is not\n        going to fix it.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "      * There is no directory in /usr/lib to hold the .so's, meaning\n        this specification can only work for python-central.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "      * There is no directory to hold data depending on the Python\n        version.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "      * And, worst of all, this stuff is incredibly complicated.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "        Implementing this and the compatibility layer will probably\n        double the codebase of python-support.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": " I believe the reason of\n        python-supports success is that it just works, and I dont\n        think I can keep the bug list so short while increasing the\n        codebase so much.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": " Thus, its going to take more than saying\n        file conflicts to convince me to implement that.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Cheers,\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
