                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "what if I convince Matthias to use /usr/lib/pyshared?", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " I will need to send\nsome patches but I think he will accept such compromise (both\ntools have to use the same directories for .", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "py and .", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "so files to make it\nwork and since pysupport cannot use /usr/lib/pythonX.Y/site-packages,\npycentral will have to use /usr/lib/pyshared/pythonX.Y)\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">       * There is no directory to hold data depending on the Python\n>         version.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "you mean different files for python2.4 and different for python2.5 or\ndifferent files for python <= 2.4 and different for >= 2.5?\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "If the first one, then how about simply installing all files to\n/usr/lib/pythonX.Y/site-packages and if second one...", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": " well, didn't you\nwant to keep pysupport simple?", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": " (BTW: is it possible in pysupport now?)\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": ">         Implementing this and the compatibility layer will probably\n>         double the codebase of python-support.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": " I believe the reason of\n>         python-supports success is that it just works, and I dont\n>         think I can keep the bug list so short while increasing the\n>         codebase so much.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": " Thus, its going to take more than saying\n>         file conflicts to convince me to implement that.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "seriously, it's not that bad, and please remember that for now I just\nwant to have all files in the same directory, we'll think about\nstandardizing other stuff later (unless you really want to discuss it now)\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
